<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-735CF642-FBC3-4F8E-8A57-A64EAB6855F2" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-735CF642-FBC3-4F8E-8A57-A64EAB6855F2" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to submit .print jobs without a RIP</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-9C631935-A322-4774-A553-6D0B52308454"><p class="- topic/p ">In case of issue with customer jobs, a .print file can be collected on site and then submitted to another printer for troubleshooting with the Colorado x DotPrint Job Submitter software (i.e, no RIP is needed). 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-6FFF84E6-9384-41AC-A15B-AB7F5D468979" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Retrieve and unzip the Colorado DotPrint Job Submitter 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Colorado DotPrint Job Submitter application can be downloaded from this web page. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><ph varid="graphiPLAZA_Support" translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><xref href="https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/support/service-support/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/support/service-support/</xref></ph> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Select "Printer support - service access", the printer type from the menu and login with your credentials. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Unzip it on a convenient workstation and location. 
</p></li></ul></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Check this requirement for the submitter tool installation: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The .NET 4.6.1 framework must be installed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="Check.Net" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C09C1F38-A74C-40FD-A1B9-0BBBD00A3370.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 11 How to check which .NET version is installed?>11 How to check which .NET version is installed</xref>. 
</p></li></ul></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Get a .print test job for troubleshooting: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Get a .print file from the customer 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="GetJobData" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-279766E4-2950-4DFB-8398-989A2744FA99.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to save received job data?>How to save received job data</xref>. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Media type used by customer 
</p></li></ul></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-CC2486E9-E593-4DE9-907E-7BF8FE167E9F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure</title><note id="GUID-BEA7452C-8513-42DE-9A02-382B60545278" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">In this instruction we use version 1.2.0 of the tool. 
</p></note><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-E8683A97-CFAA-42AC-B15B-8375DE8C5137" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Browse to the location where you unzipped the Colorado x_PrintJobSubmitter_Rx.y.zip file. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Double-click Colorado.DotPrintJobSubmitter.exe to start the application. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-6D92E2C7-DCC6-41CF-BDC6-8A8BE24F6056" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DEB77EA0-949B-4A5C-BD24-C7DC92A088CC-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DEB77EA0-949B-4A5C-BD24-C7DC92A088CC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In the Hostname field, type in the printer IP address or hostname 
</p><fig id="GUID-DCDCCFD5-5E73-4C8A-B7B5-3A8EB3CFEDE4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6755797E-BA49-483F-8096-1E088E817E38-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6755797E-BA49-483F-8096-1E088E817E38-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Connect: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If the connection to the printer is successful, the Submit button is accessible 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If the connection failed, the Submit button remains greyed out 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-C880B64D-A354-49D7-97AC-495B5A5FB8F1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-11A4196B-AEF8-45A7-B0EB-D31444A337F0-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-11A4196B-AEF8-45A7-B0EB-D31444A337F0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" morerows="16" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Browse to locate and select the .print file to submit. 
</p><fig id="GUID-59CAF33C-CA9D-46EA-A419-2EEADB3DCFB4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-540899BA-D4BD-4CF1-8D40-9923DF4F4BFA-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-540899BA-D4BD-4CF1-8D40-9923DF4F4BFA-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Displayed information is: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Image size, Width and Height, in pixels 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Roll width in microns 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Print mode, displayed as Print mode Id 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Check the table below for the corresponding Colorado Print Mode: 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Print Mode ID (.print file) 
</b> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Print mode</b> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">??? 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
